(34, 1, '2015-07-29 02:05:16', '2015-07-29 02:05:16', '<h4>Who says the â€˜burbs canâ€™t be cool?</h4>\r\nSuburban Burger has cool written all over it!<a href="http://111.93.163.213/SuburbanBurger/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/SUB-BURG-Bar.jpg"><img class="img-thumbnail alignright" src="http://111.93.163.213/SuburbanBurger/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/SUB-BURG-Bar-300x187.jpg" alt="SUB-BURG-Bar" width="300" height="187" /></a>\r\nOur edgy new restaurant boasts the best of the â€˜burbs. From our people to our produce, as much as possible is locally sourced, or purchased from small local business. Thereâ€™s no reason to head into town to experience what Melbourne has to offer.\r\nFrom the ground up, Suburban Burger has the heart and soul of the suburbs surging through its bloodstream. From the moment you enter, youâ€™re surrounded by furniture made from recycled materials scrounged locally and crafted by Andy &amp; Scott, owner and barman, over a four month period.\r\nYouâ€™ll be served by our Family (thereâ€™s no crew in our restaurant!) made up of more than 50 local people dedicated to making your experience unforgettable.\r\nSo, whilst you might not see our gourmet burgers lit up in lights on billboards, youâ€™ll know theyâ€™ve been made with love by local people using local produce.\r\nAre they the best burgers youâ€™ll ever eat? We like to think so. They each have an identity and are dripping with so much personality, youâ€™ll want to friend them all on Facebook, or maybe even Tinder', 'About Us', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'about-us', '', '', '2015-08-07 02:47:17', '2015-08-07 02:47:17', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/SuburbanBurger/php/?page_id=34', 0, 'page', '', 0),
